---

<section id="law" class="bg-sand border-y border-black/5 py-16 md:py-20 px-6 scroll-mt-16">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 md:gap-16 items-start">

    <!-- Left: Legal framing -->
    <div>
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-gray-600 mb-2">The legal framework</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        California law is on our side
      </h2>

      <span class="inline-block bg-forest-ghost text-forest-deep text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded mb-4">
        Fair Play in Community Sports Act &nbsp;·&nbsp; AB 2404 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Gov. Code § 53080
      </span>

      <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-forest-mid bg-white px-4 py-3 rounded-r-lg text-base text-gray-600 italic leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Cities may not discriminate by gender in how they run youth sports and allocate
        public fields, lights, restrooms, storage, and access. Girls' programs are entitled
        to facilities equal in quality and scope to what boys' programs receive.
      </blockquote>

      <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Courts weigh the whole picture — fields, lighting, scheduling, cost, and access —
        not any single item. Other California cities have closed gaps like these by adding
        lights, fencing, and amenities, and by ending arrangements that lock one program into
        second-class facilities. Claremont can too.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: The two asks -->
    <div id="ordinance" class="scroll-mt-16">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-gray-600 mb-2">What we're asking for</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">
        Two clear actions from City Council
      </h2>

      <!-- Ask 1 -->
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-forest-ghost text-forest-deep text-xs font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Repeal Chapter 11.08</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              The 1995 ordinance restricts La Puerta Sports Park lighting to soccer practice only
              and caps girls' softball at four Sunday permits per year. It's written into city law —
              and until it's gone, nothing else can move forward.
            </p>
            <a
              href="https://ecode360.com/43830587"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-forest-mid hover:text-forest mt-3 transition-colors"
            >
              Read Ordinance 11.08<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 6H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 003 8.25v10.5A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h10.5A2.25 2.25 0 0018 18.75V10.5m-10.5 6L21 3m0 0h-5.25M21 3v5.25" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Ask 2 -->
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-forest-ghost text-forest-deep text-xs font-semibold flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Commit to equal facilities on a real timeline</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Girls' softball deserves correctly sized fields with lights, fencing, secured grounds,
              and the same access and permit rules everyone else gets — with a published,
              enforceable timeline from the City.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
